newsitem.title: USA: U.S. cash soymeal-Active to moderate trade seen.
newsitem.headline: U.S. cash soymeal-Active to moderate trade seen.

text.p: Most soymeal basis offers were unchanged Thursday and dealers reported moderate to active trading in both rail and truck markets.
"People were waiting for a rush of demand after July went off the board (CBOT) and now we're starting to see some of that," a dealer said.
Brokers said that expected downtimes for summer maintenance and tightening supplies of old crop soybeans in the U.S. and Brazil should support basis levels in the near-term.
The National Oilseed Processors Association will release the weekly crush at 0700 CDT on Friday.
Trade sources expected the crush to fall between 20.25 to 24.00 million bushels. That figure compares with last week's crush of 21.871 million.
Sources whose estimates fell at the high end of the range said the recent improvement in crush margins caused some processors to crush more soybeans.
